# **Parenting Support Specialist/Mentor for Pregnant & Parenting Youth**

## **JOB DESCRIPTION: PARENTING SUPPORT SPECIALIST/MENTOR (HYBRID ROLE)**

### **Position Overview**

The Parenting Support Specialist/Mentor provides specialized support services to pregnant and parenting youth in foster care through a dual-generation approach. This hybrid position combines parenting education, mentorship, and case coordination while maintaining flexibility for other compatible responsibilities. Working under the leadership of our Program Director, who brings both professional expertise and personal parenting experience, this role ensures young parents receive trauma-informed support that promotes positive outcomes for both parent and child.

### **Primary Objectives**

* **\[T3C\]** Deliver specialized parenting support as an add-on to primary Service Packages  
* **\[TBRI\]** Implement trauma-informed care addressing intergenerational trauma impacts  
* **\[TAC 749\]** Ensure compliance with documentation and service requirements  
* Support pregnant and parenting youth ages 14-22 through practical, achievable goals  
* **\[CQI\]** Contribute to program development and continuous improvement  
* Foster healthy parent-child relationships through evidence-based interventions

### **Key Responsibilities**

**Direct Service Delivery (50-60% of role)**

* **\[T3C\]** Provide individualized parenting education and support  
* Conduct comprehensive assessments for pregnant and parenting youth  
* **\[TBRI\]** Apply trauma-informed approaches to parent-child relationships  
* Facilitate parent-child interaction coaching and bonding activities  
* **\[TAC 749\]** Document all services and engagement efforts  
* Respond to parenting-related crises with appropriate support

**Care Coordination (20-25% of role)**

* **\[T3C\]** Coordinate healthcare including prenatal care and well-child visits  
* Navigate complex benefit systems (WIC, SNAP, Medicaid, childcare)  
* Connect youth to Early Childhood Intervention when appropriate  
* **\[RCC\]** Partner with community resources for comprehensive support  
* Ensure STAR Health enrollment for infants  
* Support educational continuity despite parenting responsibilities

**Foster Home Support (10-15% of role)**

* Consult with foster parents on supporting young parent-child dyads  
* **\[T3C\]** Provide guidance on balancing support with youth autonomy  
* Address multi-generational household dynamics  
* Train foster families on dual-generation trauma impacts  
* Support emergency response for pregnancy/infant care needs

**Program Development (10-15% of role)**

* **\[TAC 749\]** Participate in CQI activities and outcome tracking  
* Contribute to Logic Model refinement based on service experience  
* Develop youth-friendly educational materials  
* **\[T3C\]** Collaborate with Program Director on service enhancements  
* Gather youth feedback for program improvement

### **Hybrid Role Flexibility**

This position may combine parenting support specialist duties with:

* General case management responsibilities  
* Transition support services for older youth  
* Community outreach and partnership development  
* Training coordination activities  
* Quality improvement projects

**Caseload Structure:**

* Maximum 20 pregnant/parenting youth for primary specialist duties  
* Additional responsibilities balanced per agency's mixed caseload system  
* Emphasis on quality over quantity during program development  
* Flexibility to adjust based on youth needs and program growth

### **Qualifications**

**Required**

* Bachelor's degree in social work, human services, child development, or related field  
* **\[TAC 749\]** Meet minimum qualifications for case management staff  
* 2+ years experience in child welfare, maternal health, or family support  
* Knowledge of child development and parent-child attachment  
* **\[TBRI\]** Willingness to complete trauma-informed care training  
* Understanding of adolescent development and young parent challenges  
* Computer skills for documentation and benefit applications

**Preferred**

* Experience with pregnant/parenting teens or young adults  
* Knowledge of maternal/infant health systems  
* Familiarity with benefit programs (WIC, SNAP, Medicaid)  
* **\[T3C\]** Understanding of Texas foster care system  
* Personal or professional experience with young parenthood  
* Bilingual capabilities (Spanish/English)  
* Group facilitation skills

### **Core Competencies**

* Non-judgmental approach to young parenthood  
* Dual-generation perspective  
* Crisis intervention skills  
* Resource navigation expertise  
* Cultural humility and responsiveness  
* Collaborative problem-solving  
* Patience and persistence in engagement

### **Working Conditions**

* Combination of office and field work  
* Regular home visits to observe parent-child interactions  
* Standard business hours with some flexibility for youth schedules  
* Occasional evening/weekend activities  
* On-call rotation for parenting emergencies  
* Local travel required  
* Valid driver's license and reliable transportation

### **Supervision and Support**

* Reports to: Program Director (Kelsey Batista, LCPAA)  
* Benefits from Program Director's combined administrative and parenting expertise  
* Receives regular supervision focused on dual-generation approach  
* Participates in team meetings and case consultation  
* Access to specialized training in parent-child interventions

### **Performance Expectations \- Year 1**

* Complete required training within specified timeframes  
* Successfully engage minimum 75% of referred youth  
* Ensure 90% healthcare compliance for parents and children  
* Achieve 85% benefit enrollment rate for eligible services  
* Maintain documentation meeting compliance standards  
* Demonstrate positive youth engagement and satisfaction

### **What Makes This Role Unique**

* Work with resilient young parents navigating dual developmental tasks  
* Support two generations simultaneously \- parent and child  
* Partner with experienced Program Director who understands parenting challenges  
* Build program from ground up with opportunity to shape services  
* Make tangible difference in breaking intergenerational cycles  
* Balance structure with flexibility based on youth needs

### **Professional Growth Opportunities**

* Year 1: Master core competencies and build program foundation  
* Year 2: Contribute to program expansion and specialization  
* Year 3: Potential leadership in training and mentoring new staff  
* Ongoing: Development of expertise in dual-generation interventions

### **Why This Role Matters**

Young parents in foster care face unique challenges requiring specialized support. This position offers the opportunity to:

* Promote healthy attachment between young parents and their children  
* Prevent intergenerational involvement in child welfare systems  
* Support educational and economic stability for young families  
* Build protective factors that last a lifetime  
* Honor the strength and potential of young parents

---

*This position represents a unique opportunity to join a developing program under experienced leadership. The hybrid nature allows for professional growth while maintaining focus on the critical mission of supporting young parent-child dyads in foster care.*
